    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Will this help?</p>\n\n<pre><code>Integer.parseInt(\"00ff00\", 16)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><code>16</code> means that you should interpret the string as 16-based (hexadecimal). By using <code>2</code> you can parse binary number, <code>8</code> stands for octal. <code>10</code> is default and parses decimal numbers.</p>\n\n<p>In your case <code>Integer.parseInt(primary.getFullHex(), 16)</code> won't work due to <code>0x</code> prefix prepended by <code>getFullHex()</code> - get rid of and you'll be fine.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 764902,
      "reputation" : 21539,
      "user_id" : 782719,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 88,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/19f3ca4c9423065b686cbbd3374d4fdb?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "GETah",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/782719/getah"
