    "last_activity_date" : 1341689025,
    "creation_date" : 1341689025,
    "answer_id" : 11377985,
    "question_id" : 11377944,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This should do it:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String hex = \"FA\"; \nint intValue = Integer.parseInt(hex, 16);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And if you want to generate hex representation of an integer, use </p>\n\n<pre><code>String hex = Integer.toHexString(12); \n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 552427,
      "reputation" : 11578,
      "user_id" : 917548,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2bbc7f5755f5f6bacceedd955404214a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Roger Lindsj&#246;",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/917548/roger-lindsj%c3%b6"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1341689050,
    "creation_date" : 1341689050,
    "answer_id" : 11377988,
    "question_id" : 11377944,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The <em>parseInt</em> method only accepts the number part, not any kind of \"base\" indicator such as \"0x\" for hexadecimal or \"0\" for octal. Use it like this</p>\n\n<pre><code>int decimal = Integer.parseInt(\"1234\", 10);\nint octal = Integer.parseInt(\"1234\", 8);\nint hex = Integer.parseInt(\"1234\", 16);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
